## 9. Roll vs. Close Decision Framework

| Situation | Action |
|---|---|
| At 50% profit | Close — buy back CC, redeploy |
| Stock rallying toward strike with >7 DTE | Consider rolling up and out (higher strike, later expiry) |
| Stock rallying through strike near expiry | Let it get called away OR roll out aggressively |
| Stock dropping sharply | CC expires worthless, sell new CC lower — more premium |
| Earnings approaching after open | Close early or roll past earnings |

---

## 10. Trade Decision

### Checklist
- [ ] IV is elevated enough for meaningful premium
- [ ] Strike is above key resistance (or accepted capping risk)
- [ ] No earnings in the window (or risk explicitly accepted)
- [ ] Getting called away at this strike is an acceptable outcome
- [ ] Annualized return ≥20% on cost basis
- [ ] Liquidity is acceptable
- [ ] Cost basis recovery plan is realistic

**Decision:** ✅ SELL CC / ⚠️ WAIT / ❌ HOLD SHARES ONLY

**Rationale:**
> _One paragraph. Why this strike, this DTE, this premium?_

